      "writtenOn": "2020-11-14T20:28:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "`init` is a golang concept which is called during the import time and it is imported in appengine/main.go (see the downstream CL) which means task is registered when the service starts.\n\nTL;DR: what this code is doing is that. \n\nIt register a new Task class `RefreshProjectConfigTask`. Everytime when we add a task with a RefreshProjectConfigTask message as its payload, CV will send a task to a queue named `refresh-project-config` in Cloud Task. \n\nIt will also install a handler at path \u0027$RoutingPrefx/refresh-project-config\u0027 (we use the default value for RoutingPrefix in the latest PS which is /internal/tasks/t/) for CV. Cloud Task will then call CV at that path with the serialized RefreshProjectConfigTask message.",
      "parentUuid": "669f0616_f12653c7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 37,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 37,
        "endChar": 9
      },
      "revId": "9b7920e0d3db0be40fb9806793500235779ef90e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
